[I] Opus audio codec

[T] Opus is a codec for interactive speech and audio transmission over the
[T] Internet.
[T]
[T] Opus can handle a wide range of interactive audio applications, including
[T] Voice over IP, videoconferencing, in-game chat, and even remote live
[T] music performances. It can scale from low bit-rate narrowband speech to
[T] very high quality stereo music.

[U] https://www.opus-codec.org/

[A] Xiphorus <team@xiph.org>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/multimedia
[F] CROSS

[E] opt doxygen graphviz

